{"key":"post-16100541","value":"<?xml version=\"1.0\"?>\n<post>\n<id>16100541</id>\n<content>Lots of bad info above.&amp;nbsp; &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;It's true that bulk substrates such as manure don't need to be cased to perform well with &lt;i&gt;P cubensis&lt;/i&gt;, but if one is going to case, the substrate does not need to be fully colonized first.&amp;nbsp; Some of the old teks called for casing at the same time as the bulk substrate is mixed, while others call for casing at 80% to 100% colonization.&amp;nbsp; It really doesn't matter much, and depending on conditions, either will work well, as will no casing layer at all.&lt;br /&gt;RR</content>\n<name>RogerRabbit</name>\n<next>16100576</next>\n<prev>16099571</prev>\n<first>16099331</first>\n<last>21808454</last>\n<when>1334650377</when>\n<utime>04/17/12 11:12 AM</utime>\n</post>"}